spec: socket_extra159
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra158.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) / AF_INET6.__eq__(30) / SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) / SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) / AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') / SOCK_STREAM.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SocketKind') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra157.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) / IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) / IPPROTO_IP.__eq__(0) / SOL_SOCKET.__eq__(65535) / SO_REUSEADDR.__eq__(4) / SO_KEEPALIVE.__eq__(8) (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') / __spec__.name.__eq__('socket') / socket.socket makefile/__setblocking/__settimeout/__getpeername/__getsockname/__setsockopt qualnames and lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra155.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.setdefaulttimeout/__class__.__name__/__module__ / getdefaulttimeout/__class__.__name__ / gethostname/__class__.__name__/__module__ / getaddrinfo/__class__.__name__/__module__ / socket.socket.__doc__/__class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra158."
    - "Wave 341 theme: socket.socket class identity (class-level, not an instance) — socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__module__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('socket') / socket.__bases__[0].__module__.__eq__('_socket') / socket.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.__init__') / socket.connect.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.connect'); socket.socket is a Python class inheriting from _socket.socket (C implementation)."
    - "socket.socket.__name__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__module__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__bases__[0].__module__ == '_socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__init__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__init__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.connect.__qualname__ == 'socket.connect'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__name__ == 'socket' (6 chars). socket.socket.__module__ == 'socket' (6 chars). socket.socket.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'socket' (6 chars). All three are the string 'socket'! The socket.socket class is defined in Lib/socket.py as: class socket(_socket.socket). The class name is 'socket', it lives in the 'socket' module, and its base class (_socket.socket) is also named 'socket' (from the _socket C module). This triple identity (class name == module name == base class name) is an unusual pattern."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__bases__[0].__module__ == '_socket' (7 chars = '_'=1 + 'socket'=6). The Python socket.socket class inherits from _socket.socket (the C implementation in Modules/socketmodule.c). The C class is named 'socket' in the '_socket' module. The '__module__' of the base class is '_socket' (with leading underscore), not 'socket'. This 7-char module name ('_socket') is 1 char longer than 'socket' (6 chars)."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__init__.__qualname__ == 'socket.__init__' (15 chars = 'socket.'=7 + '__init__'=8). socket.socket.__init__ is a Python function (not a C wrapper_descriptor), because socket.socket is defined in pure Python (Lib/socket.py). Its __init__ is defined in Python and sets up the socket. This contrasts with struct.Struct.__init__ which is a wrapper_descriptor (C type). socket.socket.connect.__qualname__ == 'socket.connect' (14 chars = 'socket.'=7 + 'connect'=7). connect is a method_descriptor (inherited from _socket.socket). The class prefix is 'socket.' (7 chars = class name 'socket' + '.'), the same length as 'Struct.' for struct.Struct methods."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

